tags.description: Head up the tiny seam up the black streak, passed the small ledge and over the large summit block. Montez la petite fissure dans la bande noire, passe la petite vire et continuez par-dessus le gros bloc au sommet.
tags.name: Sutounu

tags.description: Head up the seam (2 glue-ins) which widens a bit, at the small ledge, take the crack on that splits off to the right, Up and over the summit blocks. Montez la petite fissure (2 scellements) qui agrandie un peu, passe la petite vire, prenez la fourche a d
tags.name: A nous deux

tags.description: Start in a vertical crack to the left of the Menhir block, Head up to the small ledge and continue onto another vertical crack leading to the right of the large summit block.  Débutez dans la fissure verticale a la gauche du bloc de Menhir, continuez pass
tags.name: Gromlech

tags.description: Start off on a block and followup to a right diagonal traverse to a flake and small corner to the top.  Grimpez au sommet du bloc et suivez le petit coin qui part par la droite, passé les encrages, suivez le coin/fissure jusqu'en haut.
tags.name: Menhir

tags.description: Bouldery start to thin crack.Mantle to glue in,move a bit right then work your way up the aesthetic crack and good holds.Nicest 5.9 of Labedan and a must do if comfy with the rating. Départ délicat en bloc pour protéger dans la petite fissure.Rétablir so
tags.name: Interruption

tags.description: This is a linkup starting in Interruption and finishing on Le Revenant. Once on the second vertical crack, traverse right near the horizontal to Le Revenant.  Variation du départ dans Interruption et finir sur Le Revenant. Une fois dans la deuxième fissur
tags.name: Sans-Nom

tags.description: Hard, Engaged and Sustained, be careful of a fall between the first and second bolt.  Difficile, engageant et soutenu, a faire attention d'une chute entre la première et deuxième plaquette.
tags.name: Le Revenant

tags.description: Head up the vertical crack of Trident and crossover left to the depression when you reach the horizontal crack.  Montez dans Trident et en arrivant a la fissure horizontale, traversez a gauche dans la dépression/fissure verticale.
tags.name: Huggies Stay Dry

tags.description: Punch through the low crux to good holds and a rest ledge. Continue to follow the crack through some moderate climbing. Finish up a wide crack to the bolted anchor.
tags.name: Trident

tags.description: Follow the right leaning diagonal intrusion, some key holds have broken, making the journey even more complex. There's a possibility of adding a couple pieces in the cracks you cross to make it a bit less heady.
tags.name: Intrusion Direct

tags.description: Start off in a small corner left of the offwidth follow up by a left traverse to a thin vertical crack. Traverse right on a horizontal and follow the bolted face to the top anchor.
tags.name: L'Envouté / Yukon BC

tags.description: Climb the bolted face just left of the offwidth Momo. the FA finished on Momo but it's also possible to linkup with l'Envoute.
tags.name: Les Mouches noires

tags.description: Time for giving your body to the crack gods, forget the face and just dive in!
tags.name: Momo

tags.description: This is a fun line with a few punches to pack. Gain the incipient finger crack which offers locks and gear. Once the crack runs out, place a piece and then step right to gain another crack. Climb this past a a few difficulties to another short step right
tags.name: Trilogie

tags.description: Starts off below a glue in on delicate moves up to some larger cracks.
tags.name: Fruitée

tags.description: Follow the glue-ins through an overhang. Finish in the vertical crack.
tags.name: Gueule de loup

tags.description: Start at the right side of the large horizontal, pull onto the slab, follow the corner up to a horizontal where you can head up the delicate face.
tags.name: Marché noir

tags.description: Go up some technical face moves to a vertical crack. Some placements can be a bit blind so whatch your moves.
tags.name: Directissime

tags.description: Follow the crack and corner moves, just left of the arrete.
tags.name: Rive gauche

tags.description: Start on the right side of the corner and make your way to the left of the arete and follow the ramp to the same belay as Rive Gauche.
tags.name: LÉperon

tags.description: Follow the face on the right of the arete.
tags.name: Babord tribord

tags.description: Up the corner to the top, optionaly you can also veer left on the face towards the top to reach Babord Tribord's anchor.
tags.name: Le Dièdre

tags.description: Climb up the crack under the roof to a small ledge, Exit the roof on its left side at the seam (bolt), Follow the crack to the dihedral then follow the path of least resistance to the anchor on the right face.
tags.name: Le Rampart

tags.description: Head up the face below the roof, climb out of the roof towards the corner, Follow the corner to the top.
tags.name: Le Surplomb

tags.description: Climb the face just to the right of the corner and overhang of Le Surplomb.
tags.name: Mr. Sécuriter

tags.description: Clip the first two glue ins of Le Gouffre and then keep to the prow on the left.
tags.name: Mini Superman

tags.description: Come to dark side and dive into it head on.
tags.name: Le Gouffre

tags.description: Sport route on the right side of the chimney.
tags.name: Souvenir

tags.description: Starts in the broken up section right of a small roof on the right of Souvenir. Followup the corners to a thin vertical crack seam to the top.
tags.name: Renversante

tags.description: Start up a slaby face to a Vee notch in a small roof, keep climbing the face trending left to a thin crack to the top.  It's also possible to start the route below the rectangular notch in the roof on the left (top-rope).
tags.name: L'Entre deux

tags.description: Start right of the roofs of Entre Deux, step around the next roof, keep heading up the face to the small ledge and top.
tags.name: Plein les mains

tags.description: Head up the face with the glue-ins left of Beding Bedang corner, at the fourth glue in, traverse a bit left and head straight up some sweet flakes and holds.
tags.name: L'Abeille

tags.description: The name comes from the first ascent party trying to free it ground up without bolts, lets say they rethinking the fixed pro idea. Start up on the right side of a slaby section into a corner, just keep to the line to the top.
tags.name: Beding bedang
